a.n: Les Migrants Ne Savent Pas Nager

p.d: June 2016. The UN announces that more than 10,000 migrants have died in the Mediterranean since 2014. The "Aquarius" is chartered by the organisation SOS Méditerranée to save lives between the Sicilian and African coasts. Two journalists are aboard, recording the commitment and distress of the crew and passengers. Directed by: Jean-Paul Mari, Frank Dhelens (France, 2016)
